oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Grand Ole Opry - Prince Albert - 1955-10-29 - Part 2
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Part 2 of Prince Albert tobacco sponsored Grand Ole Opry segment from October 29, 1955. Featuring Grant Turner (announcer), Little Jimmy Dickens (host/performer), guest performers the Wilburn Brothers, and regular performers Rod Brasfield, Tommy Jackson, Del Wood, Minnie Pearl, and Chet Atkins. Held at Ryman Auditorium, Nashville, TN.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Del Wood; Minnie Pearl; Wilburn Brothers; Chet Atkins; Little Jimmy Dickens
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Why Did You Wait (incomplete, test band) -- Rocky Mountain Express (Del Wood) [continued from part 1] -- Little Jimmy Dickens introduces Minnie Pearl -- Comedy routine (Minnie Pearl, Little Jimmy Dickens) -- Little Jimmy Dickens introduces the Wilburn Brothers -- Temptation, Go Away (Wilburn Brothers) -- Little Jimmy Dickens introduces Chet Atkins -- South (Chet Atkins) -- Little Jimmy Dickens talks -- We Could (Little Jimmy Dickens) -- Closing theme -- Closing statement (Little Jimmy Dickens) -- Cavalier Cigarettes commercial -- Station announcements
